@DreierF The type for `bbox` is set to `RaphaelAxisAlignedBoundingBox`, but that interface contains only `x`, `y`, `width`, and `height` -- while the [Raphael code](https://github.com/DmitryBaranovskiy/raphael/blob/b5fdbdc9850827eb49622cd0bc81b26025f8128a/dev/raphael.core.js#L1295) accesses `x2` and `y2`.  Taking a look at source code / documentation for `getBBox`, that returns an object with the `x2` and `y2` properties, so I think we should just add

```
x2: number;
y2: number;
```

to `RaphaelAxisAlignedBoundingBox`

